comment.text: The translation key "MoveFolderItem" is used to display a success message when a folder has been successfully moved. It appears in a UI where a file or folder operation results in a successful move, such as a confirmation dialog or toast notification. The message includes the original folder name and the destination of the move.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The order of the placeholders is reversed compared to the English content. The English content has <1>{{folderName}}</1> after <2>{{title}}</2>, but the Azerbaijani translation has it the other way around.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Change the order of the placeholders to match the English content: "<2>{{title}}</2> qovluğu uğurla <1>{{folderName}}</1> qovluğuna köçürüldü" should become "<2>{{title}}</2> qovluğu uğurla <1>{{folderName}}</1> qovluğuna köçürüldü".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The curly braces for variable insertion in the Czech translation are inconsistent. `<1>` and `<2>` are used, but the original English uses `<1>` for `folderName` and `<2>` for `title`. It should be consistent with the English template.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Change `<1>{{folderName}}</1>` to `<2>{{folderName}}</2>` and `<2>{{title}}</2>` to `<1>{{title}}</1>` to match the original English order.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The angle brackets around {{title}} and {{folderName}} are inconsistent with the English content. The English uses <2> and <1> while the Japanese uses the same.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Ensure consistent angle bracket numbering across both languages. If the numbering is important for parsing or display, it should match the English: フォルダー <1>{{title}}</1> が <2>{{folderName}}</2> に正常に移動されました

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The original English content uses `<1>` for `folderName` and `<2>` for `title`. The Korean translation reverses these tags.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Adjust the tags to match the original English: `<2>{{title}}</2> 폴더가 <1>{{folderName}}</1> 폴더로 이동되었습니다

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'successfully' is missing from the Lao translation. The English sentence explicitly states a successful move.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ໄຟລ໌ <2>{{title}}</2> ຍ້າຍໄປທີ່ <1>{{folderName}}</1> ຢ່າງສະຫງ່າງາມ

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English 'moved to' is translated as 'pārvietota uz'. While technically correct, a more natural and commonly used translation in Latvian for this context would be 'nonesta uz' or 'pārvietota'.

The Dutch translation uses 'is' (present tense) instead of 'werd' (past tense) which is more appropriate given the context of a completed action.  While 'is' isn't strictly incorrect, 'werd' would more accurately reflect the successful movement.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: De map <2>{{title}}</2> werd succesvol verplaatst naar <1>{{folderName}}</1>

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The tag order is incorrect. The English content uses <2>{{title}}</2> and <1>{{folderName}}</1>, while the Polish translation uses <2>{{title}}</2> and <1>{{folderName}}</1>. This should be consistent with the English source.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Change the Polish translation to use <1>{{folderName}}</1> and <2>{{title}}</2> to match the English source.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Sinhala translation maintains the HTML tags from the English content, which is generally not desirable in natural language output. The tags should be removed.
The angle brackets around the variables {{title}} and {{folderName}} are correctly placed, mirroring the English original.

The English word 'moved' is better translated as 'премештен' in Serbian (Cyrillic) to maintain the sense of a folder being moved.  While 'премештен' is correct, a more natural phrasing would use a more conversational verb.
